The point is that you don't really know how fast a team is "pushing it" when you are using a pace # that combines both teams pace for a given game. https://t.co/XwJJFNE9oU

By using @bballbreakdown caveman style of Possession "count" GSW ranks 10th at 103.85
By using the actual time they use on offense they are ranked 1st at 11.90 seconds.

But we are trying to measure how fast a team is playing, not how fast their opponents are also playing. Why not use the one # that only measures their pace? cmon guys this isn't that hard. https://t.co/Qbvs6WcjZ9

My point was if we are going to make sweeping statements like "fast teams don't win" we should at least try and use actual stats that capture how fast a team is playing not how fast a game was played by both teams.
